snippet.title: 2016 McDONALD'S RABBIDS SET OF 8 HAPPY MEAL KIDS TOYS U.S. REVIEW
snippet.description:
Here at Kids Meal Toys we review the 2015-2016 McDonald's Rabbids Complete Set Of 8 Happy Meal Toys available at restaurants in the U.S. and Canada from late December 2015 to January 2016.

2015 - 2016 McDonald's Rabbids Happy Meal Box. This is the US McDonald's (USA version) of the Rabbids Happy Meal Box.
https://youtu.be/Lm-2BNHS1I0

2015 McDonald's Rabbids Invasion Happy Meal Box Latin America / Mexico. The happy meal box comes from McDonald's Mexico and it is known as Cajita Feliz Juguetes in Spanish.
https://youtu.be/EB3XFM7Oz9w

2015 McDonald's Rabbids Invasion complete set of 9 Happy Meal toys Latin America / Mexico / Brazil. The Rabbids are Rabid Rabbits!
https://youtu.be/zuX-denx28Y

The Nickelodeon Raving Rabbids Invasion McDonalds Happy Meal toys are available in countries in Latin America such as Mexico and Brazil (Brasil). They are known as Cajita Feliz Juguetes and McLanche Feliz Brinquedos Brindes. The Rayman Raving Rabbids are produced by Ubisoft and come from France, in French it is called les lapins crétins invasion jouets joyeux festin. The Rabbids name most likely comes from Rabid Rabbits / Rabids, or silly cretin rabbits!

In the USA and Canada, the Rabbids happy meal toys (complete set of 8) will be available in late December 2015 to January 2016 along with the happy meal toys for girls, the McDonald's Shopkins happy meal toys.

Music by Incompetech under creative commons.
Editing by KidsMealToys.

Please like and subscribe! :)

Kids Meal Toys is a family friendly channel, so please join us on our next kids meal toys collection adventure! We review mostly kids meal toys and fast food toys, including the most popular McDonald's Happy Meal toys. Subscribe today! :)

Thanks for watching!

Kids Meal Toys.

snippet.title: Marvel Studios' Captain America: Civil War
snippet.description: Marvel's Captain America: Civil War finds Steve Rogers leading the newly formed team of Avengers in their continued efforts to safeguard humanity. But after another incident involving the Avengers results in collateral damage, political pressure mounts to install a system of accountability, headed by a governing body to oversee and direct the team. The new status quo fractures the Avengers, resulting in two camps-one led by Steve Rogers and his desire for the Avengers to remain free to defend humanity without government interference, and the other following Tony Stark's surprising decision to support government oversight and accountability.
